{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/easy-text-to-speech-with-python-bfb34250036e", "time": 1683001373.602557, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/easy-text-to-speech-with-python-bfb34250036e/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Easy Text-to-Speech with Python. Text to Speech | by Dhilip Subramanian | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Easy Text-to-Speech with Python", "description": "Text-to-speech (TTS) technology reads aloud digital text. It can take words on computers, smartphones, tablets and convert them into audio. Also, all kinds of text files can be read aloud, including\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://gtts.readthedocs.io/en/latest/module.html", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 2}, {"url": "https://gtts.readthedocs.io/en/latest/module.html", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 5}, {"url": "https://www.kdnuggets.com/2020/05/easy-text-speech-python.html", "anchor_text": "KDnuggets", "paragraph_index": 15}, {"url": "http://www.sdhilip.com", "anchor_text": "www.sdhilip.com", "paragraph_index": 17}], "all_paragraphs": ["Text-to-speech (TTS) technology reads aloud digital text. It can take words on computers, smartphones, tablets and convert them into audio. Also, all kinds of text files can be read aloud, including Word, pages document, online web pages can be read aloud. TTS can help kids who struggle with reading. Many tools and apps are available to convert text into speech.", "Python comes with a lot of handy and easily accessible libraries and we\u2019re going to look at how we can deliver text-to-speech with Python in this article.", "Different API\u2019s are available in Python in order to convert text to speech. One of Such API\u2019s is the Google Text to Speech commonly known as the gTTS API. It is very easy to use the library which converts the text entered, into an audio file which can be saved as a mp3 file. It supports several languages and the speech can be delivered in any one of the two available audio speeds, fast or slow. More details can be found here", "Import gTTS library and \u201cos\u201d module in order to play the converted audio", "Creating a text that we want to convert into audio", "gTTS supports multiple languages. Please refer to the documentation here. Selected \u2018en\u2019 -> English and stored in the language variable", "Creating an object called speech and passing the text and language to the engine. Marked slow = False which tells the module that the converted audio should have a high speed.", "Saving the converted audio in a mp3 file named called \u2018text.mp3\u2019", "Playing the converted file, using Windows command \u2018start\u2019 followed by the name of the mp3 file.", "Here, covert the text file into speech. Reading the text file and pass to gTTS module", "Reading the text file and store into object called text. My file name is \u201cdraft.txt\u201d", "Passing the text file into gTTS module and store into speech", "Saving the converted audio in a mp3 file named called \u2018voice.mp3\u2019", "GTTS is an easy tool to convert text to voice, but it requires an internet connection to operate because it depends entirely on Google to get the audio data.", "Thanks for reading. Keep learning and stay tuned for more!", "You can also read this article on KDnuggets.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Business Intelligence Consultant | Data Engineer | www.sdhilip.com"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fbfb34250036e&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Feasy-text-to-speech-with-python-bfb34250036e&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"